snippet.textDisplay: Gonna be honest here. I know nothing about Kobe other than he was a basketball player. I live in Belgium where basketball isn’t nearly as popular as it is in the States and other than Michael Jordan, LeBron James and maybe a few others, Kobe Bryant was one of the few ball players who’s name would be familiar to a novice’s ear here. so when the news came he died, especially at such a young age, it was surprising, shocking sure, but not nearly as shocking as it is to the people  who really were familiar with him, both personally or in his celebrity status. It felt just like ‘huh, another celebrity passed’. But as I’m listening to Jimmy talking about Kobe  with the crack in his voice, genuinely upset by this loss, I’m tearing up. Because I can really feel what he meant to people. And losing someone, anyone, who generates such love, inspiration and meaning to so many people all over the world, is always a terrible waste. RIP Kobe. May you inspire as many people in death as you did in life.
